Task 1: Environment Preparation and Tool Installation
Subtask 1.1: System Update and Preparation
First, ensure your system is updated and prepare the environment for security tool installation.

# Update system packages
sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y

# Install essential dependencies
sudo apt install -y curl wget gnupg2 software-properties-common apt-transport-https ca-certificates

# Create directories for our lab
mkdir -p ~/incident-response-lab/{logs,scripts,evidence,reports}
cd ~/incident-response-lab
Subtask 1.2: Install and Configure Wazuh
Wazuh serves as our central SIEM platform for log collection, analysis, and alerting.

# Add Wazuh repository
curl -s https://packages.wazuh.com/key/GPG-KEY-WAZUH | sudo apt-key add -
echo "deb https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/apt/ stable main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/wazuh.list

# Update package list
sudo apt update

# Install Wazuh manager
sudo apt install -y wazuh-manager

# Start and enable Wazuh manager
sudo systemctl enable wazuh-manager
sudo systemctl start wazuh-manager

# Install Wazuh API
sudo apt install -y wazuh-api

# Configure Wazuh API
sudo /var/ossec/api/scripts/configure_api.sh

# Start Wazuh API
sudo systemctl enable wazuh-api
sudo systemctl start wazuh-api

# Install Wazuh agent (for local monitoring)
sudo apt install -y wazuh-agent

# Configure agent to connect to local manager
sudo sed -i 's/<server>.*<\/server>/<server>127.0.0.1<\/server>/' /var/ossec/etc/ossec.conf

# Start Wazuh agent
sudo systemctl enable wazuh-agent
sudo systemctl start wazuh-agent
Subtask 1.3: Install and Configure Suricata
Suricata provides network intrusion detection and prevention capabilities.

# Install Suricata
sudo apt install -y suricata

# Update Suricata rules
sudo suricata-update

# Configure Suricata for our network interface
INTERFACE=$(ip route | grep default | awk '{print $5}' | head -1)
sudo sed -i "s/interface: eth0/interface: $INTERFACE/" /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml

# Enable JSON output for better integration
sudo sed -i 's/enabled: no/enabled: yes/' /etc/suricata/suricata.yaml

# Start Suricata
sudo systemctl enable suricata
sudo systemctl start suricata

# Verify Suricata is running
sudo systemctl status suricata
Subtask 1.4: Install and Configure Zeek
Zeek provides comprehensive network traffic analysis and logging.

# Install Zeek
sudo apt install -y zeek

# Add Zeek to PATH
echo 'export PATH=/opt/zeek/bin:$PATH' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

# Configure Zeek network interface
INTERFACE=$(ip route | grep default | awk '{print $5}' | head -1)
echo "interface=$INTERFACE" | sudo tee /opt/zeek/etc/node.cfg

# Install Zeek control scripts
sudo /opt/zeek/bin/zeekctl install

# Start Zeek
sudo /opt/zeek/bin/zeekctl start

# Verify Zeek is running
sudo /opt/zeek/bin/zeekctl status
